    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "blar\name\nPAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS, INC.\n135 EAST 42nd STREET\nNEW YORK CITY\nCLARA ADAMS carried this letter\non the Inaugural Trans-Atlantic\nPassenger Flight aboard the DIXIE\nClipper - the first leg of her\nglobe girdling air trip.\nTicket\nNo.1.\nPORTUGAL\nORREIO\nAEREO 2$50\nCOLDOG\n00021-0\nVIA AIR MAIL\n* *\n*\nCORREO AEREO\n*\n*\nFrence Lampit\nVION\n5364 sydenhan\nPhila., Pa\nU SA",
      "Captain R. 0. D. Lullevan\nDuque Clipper, Pt Washington\nR.S.\nVIA\nVIA AIR MAIL\n* *\n*\nCORREO AEREO\n*\n*\nPARAVION\n2000.05 8.1270.22",
      "PAAO\nPAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS,\nINC.\nGENERAL OFFICES - CHRYSLER BUILDING - NEW\nYORK CITY\nClara Adams is thinking of you while\nsoaring over land and sea on her world flight.\nThe Inaugural Passenger Flight across\nthe Atlantic in the Pan American Clipper \"Dixie\"\nwas a wonderful start.\nIf all goes well, I should be back in\nNew York between July 14th and 20th.\nSincerely,\nClara Adams\nAIR 22\nMAIL",
      "PAAC\nPAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS, INC.\nGENERAL OFFICES - CHRYSLER BUILDING - NEW YORK CITY\nClara Adams is thinking of you while\nsoaring over land and sea on her world flight.\nThe Inaugural Passenger Flight across\nthe Atlantic in the Pan American Clipper \"Dixie\"\nwas a wonderful start.\nIf all goes well, I should be back in\nNew York between July 14th and 20th.\nSincerely,\nClara Adams\nMAIL"
    ],
